                            <comment id="12879515" author="jukkaz" created="Wed, 16 Jun 2010 22:40:00 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;d go with XMP as much as possible. XMP leverages Exif for image metadata, and the most relevant fields are probably:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    tiff:ImageLength&lt;br/&gt;
    tiff:ImageWidth&lt;br/&gt;
    tiff:SamplesPerPixel&lt;br/&gt;
    tiff:BitsPerSample&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12879532" author="gagravarr" created="Wed, 16 Jun 2010 22:57:38 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;OK, I&apos;ll work up a patch that uses these keys, hopefully some time next week&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If you get a chance in the mean time, do please add those entries to the XMPDM class ready &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/smile.gif&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12880484" author="jukkaz" created="Sat, 19 Jun 2010 15:07:06 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;I added a new class o.a.t.metadata.TIFF for these constants. Feel free to add more entries from &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.adobe.com/devnet/xmp/pdfs/XMPSpecificationPart2.pdf&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;http://www.adobe.com/devnet/xmp/pdfs/XMPSpecificationPart2.pdf&lt;/a&gt; if needed.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12883151" author="gagravarr" created="Mon, 28 Jun 2010 15:00:26 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ve updated the parsers to use the new metadata entries, in r958581.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
